[normal] 
[normal]).  Figures in the May press release show 6,168 tenants received direct payments, the total level of rent charged stood at £19,204,022 and an improvement in the average rent collection rate to 94%- with levels of payments by tenants on the projects varying from 91% to 97%. (This compares to an average of 92% published in a December 2012 press release covering the first four months).  The demonstration projects are being independently evaluated (funded by DWP) by a research consortium, from the Centre for Regional Economic and Social Research (CRESR) at
[normal] 
[normal]Sheffield 
[normal]Hallam
[normal] University, 
[normal]the Institute of Social Policy at the University of Oxford, and 
[normal]lpsos
[normal] MORI (IM). The evaluation findings, including full rent account analysis and the operation of switch-backs are due to be published in a series of reports in 2014.
